Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setDelayFootPrint(25.10)                              setDelayFootPrint(25.10)

Name
       setDelayFootPrint - Specifies the delay cell footprint

Syntax
       setDelayFootPrint

       [-help]

       [-library <libName>]

       <names>

       Specifies  the delay cell footprint. This footprint name is usually as-
       signed during design import. The delay cells from  the  cell  footprint
       name  are used for inserting delays when you run timing optimization to
       fix hold-time violations.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each setDelayFootPrint parameter. For a detailed  de-
              scription  of the command and all of its parameters, use the man
              command:

              man setDelayFootPrint

       -library <libName>
              Specifies the library name from where the cells will  be  picked
              up.

       <names>
              Specifies  the  delay  cell footprint name or a delay cell name.
              When you specify a delay cell name, the Innovus  software  auto-
              matically finds the cell footprint name.

Example
       The following command sets the delay footprint name to DEL_1P:

       setDelayFootPrint DEL_1P

